{"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Composable Architecture is under constant development, and we are always looking for ways to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"simplify the library, and make it more powerful. This version of the library introduced 1 new"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"API, as well as beta support for Swift Testing."}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Before following this migration guide be sure you have fully migrated to the newest","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"tools of version 1.11. See ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides","isActive":true},{"text":" for more information.","type":"text"}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Important","style":"important"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Custom file storage coding","anchor":"Custom-file-storage-coding"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Version 1.10 of the Composable Architecture introduced a powerful tool for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"sharing state","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"sharing state"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/SharingState"},{"type":"text","text":" amongst your features, and included several built-in persistence"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"strategies, including file storage. This strategy, however, was not very flexible, and only"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"supported the default JSON encoding and decoding offered by Swift."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In this version, you can now define custom encoding and decoding logic using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"fileStorage(_:decode:encode:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Swift Testing","anchor":"Swift-Testing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Xcode 16 and Swift 6 come with a powerful new native testing framework. Existing test targets using","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"XCTest can even incrementally adopt the framework and define new tests with Testing. Existing XCTest","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"test ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"helpers","type":"text"}]},{"text":", however, are not compatible with the new framework, and so test tools like the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Composable Architecture’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"TestStore","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" did not work with it out of the box.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"That changes with this version, which seamlessly supports XCTest "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"and"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Swift’s Testing framework."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"You can now create a test store in a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Test"},{"type":"text","text":" and failures will be reported accordingly."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.19","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.18","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17.1","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.16","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchit